title: Unemployment clocks in at 5.7 per cent in January
text:
twitter TWEET More 
Australia's unemployment rate fell to 5.7 per cent in January, official figures show, beating expectations of it staying at 5.8 per cent. 
The total number of people with jobs rose by 13,500 in the month, the Australian Bureau of Statistics said on Thursday, with the market forecasting a rise of 15,000. SHARE Share on Twitter TWEET Link Business generic by Mayu Kanamori for AFR first use. Pic taken on 030715 for AFR generic. Full-time employment fell by 44,800 jobs, while the number of part-time jobs was up by 58,300. 
The participation rate, which refers to the number of people either employed or actively looking for work, was down at 64.6 per cent in January from 64.7 in December. Related Content
